==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Typhotoxin
<hw>Ty`pho*tox"in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Typh</ets>oid + <ets>-toxic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A basic substance, <chform>C7H17NO2</chform>, formed
from the growth of the typhoid bacillus on meat pulp. It induces in
small animals lethargic conditions with liquid dejecta.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Typhous</ent>⟦br⟧
